docs:

#### docsheader ####
text: Edit basic/funding information
----
ref: edit
#### docsstep ####
step: 1
----
text: Go to your [community settings](../#manage). By default the profile is now shown:
----
image: profile.png
#### docsstep ####
step: 2
----
text: Edit the basic information and funding information according to the following guide:

- **Name**: The title of your community which will be prominently displayed everywhere you community is linked.
- **Short description**: A short text/slogan (displayed in header).
- **Type**: Select the type of community among: project, event, topic or organisation (displayed in header).
- **Website**: Link to your website (displayed in header).
- **Organisations**: Link one or more organisations from the [ROR database](https://ror.org) to your community (enables user to browse communities by organisation).
- **Awards**: Link one or more funders or awards to your community (enables user to browse communities by funder/award).
- **Subjects**: Add one or more disciplinary subjects to your community.

#### docsstep ####
step: 3
----
text: Click **Save** button to persist the changes.

#### docsheader ####
text: Add a logo
----
ref: addlogo
#### docsstep ####
step: 1
----
text: Go to your [community settings](../#manage).
#### docsstep ####
step: 2
----
text: Click **Upload new picture** and select a picture from your computer. The logo must be smaller than 1MB.
----
image: logo.png
#### docsstep ####
step: 3
----
text: ATTENTION: Once uploaded, it can take some few moments for the logo to become visible on all pages. This is due to browse-caching and occurs on pages you have already visited.
#### docsheader ####
text: Remove a logo
----
ref: removelogo
#### docsstep ####
step: 1
----
text: Go to your [community settings](../#manage).
#### docsstep ####
step: 2
----
text: Click the red **Delete picture** button to remove a previously uploaded logo.
----
image: logo-delete.png
#### docsstep ####
step: 3
----
text: Confirm that you want to delete the picture.
----
image: logo-confirm.png

